FBIS4-327 "drafr068_c_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Tells UK Paper of Assassination Attempts Tells UK Paper of Assassination Attempts MB0804064994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 8 Apr 94 MB0804064994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Inkatha Freedom Party leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi says he has information that hit squads were sent to assassinate him in recent weeks. Dr. Buthelezi is quoted in the British newspaper, THE DAILY STAR. In an exclusive interview, Dr. Buthelezi said members of the South African Communist Party who were also members of the ANC were guilty of the attempts. He told the newspaper that he had little hope that the talks with the state president, F.W. de Klerk, and ANC leader Nelson Mandela today would produce any result.
